<dl id="n03027c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03027c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03027c"> 27(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Meldon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[St. Fursey]</font> was trained in Connaught at a monastery on the island of Inchiquin in Lough Corrib by St. Brendan, an uncle of his father&apos;s, and by <mark>St. Meldan</mark>, who succeeded St. Brendan as head of the community. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 72</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
